Photo shared by TYLER HENRI on July 04, 2021 tagging @forbes, and @thenri_. May be an image of 1 person, suit and text that says 'forbes.com Forbes T Henri founder, designer, and entrepreneur Tyler... COURTESY HENRI As writer who stares at screen more than he sleeps that's masochism. So last month decided to do something kind to my eyes (and my crow's feet) and through a serpentine search online finally stumbled across Henri, beposke start-up eyewear brand founded by design and lifestyle entrepreneur Tyler Gelb.'.

node.text: Every Entrepreneur’s Dream is to one day be recognized and published in Forbes. Reflecting back through the blood, sweat and tears of the first year’s of my startup to this point. There are 3 main factors I can attribute my success, thus far in launching in a luxury label. First, dedication beyond perspiration. This means beyond Mon-Fri : 9-5 hustling isn’t enough, you put in the extra late nights and work weekends. Time is one of the only things we cannot create more of, plan and utilize it wisely. Second is abundant positive energy exercised through across the board  consistency. Everything you do, must be in line with the laws you create. These boundaries create perpetual motion and integration of multiple moving parts. Design, define and live by your laws. Be in sync. Thirdly, is be truly different and change the world. The best solutions always arise from the best thinkers “problem-solving.” Find the problem and be the solution. Than fill that solution with disruptive innovation. | click link on Bio to view my Forbes Article #THENRI #luxuryeyewear #disruptor #luxurylifestyle #madeinjapan #handmade #fashionblogger #highfashion #fashionsunglasses
